[{"location":"flow.html#Cogeodesic-Flow-1","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"(Co)geodesic Flow","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"flow.html#","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"(Co)geodesic Flow","text":"Methods for (co)geodesic flow. These are temporary, until Manifolds.jl provides the same functionality.","category":"page"},{"location":"flow.html#","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"(Co)geodesic Flow","text":"Modules = [ManifoldHMC]\nPages = [\"flow.jl\"]\nOrder = [:type, :function]","category":"page"},{"location":"flow.html#ManifoldHMC.cogeodesic_flow!","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"ManifoldHMC.cogeodesic_flow!","text":"  cogeodesic_flow!(M, x, p, x₀, p₀, t)\n\nFollow the geodesic with initial point x_0 in M and momentum p_0 in T_x_0^* M for time t, dragging p_0 along. The resulting point and cotangent vector are stored in x and p, respectively.\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"flow.html#ManifoldHMC.cogeodesic_flow-Tuple{Any,Any,Any}","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"ManifoldHMC.cogeodesic_flow","text":"  cogeodesic_flow(M, x₀, p₀, t)\n\nFollow the geodesic with initial point x_0 in M and momentum p_0 in T_x_0^* M for time t, dragging p_0 along.\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"flow.html#ManifoldHMC.geodesic_flow!","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"ManifoldHMC.geodesic_flow!","text":"  geodesic_flow!(M, x, v, x₀, v₀, t)\n\nFollow the geodesic with initial point x_0 in M and velocity v_0 in T_x_0 M for time t, dragging v_0 along. The resulting point and tangent vector are stored in x and v, respectively.\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"flow.html#ManifoldHMC.geodesic_flow-NTuple{4,Any}","page":"(Co)geodesic Flow","title":"ManifoldHMC.geodesic_flow","text":"  geodesic_flow(M, x₀, v₀, t)\n\nFollow the geodesic with initial point x_0 in M and velocity v_0 in T_x_0 M for time t, dragging v_0 along.\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#Introduction-1","page":"Overview","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"ManifoldHMC provides functionality for Hamiltonian Monte Carlo (HMC) on manifolds. For an overview of HMC, we recommend reading [Betancourt, 2017]. For an introduction to HMC on manifolds, we recommend reading [Byrne and Girolami, 2013].","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"This package provides a minimal feature set to join together two general-purpose packages:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"DynamicHMC.jl implements the approach to \"Dynamic HMC\" described in [Betancourt, 2017] and implemented in Stan.\nManifolds.jl is an under-development package that provides a general framework for programming on manifolds.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"The primary purpose of this package is to generalize existing implementations of HMC, enabling the efficient dynamic HMC approach with automated tuning during a warm-up period to be applied when sampling parameters that are not defined in a Euclidean space but instead defined on such manifolds as the n-sphere, the n-simplex, and the space of positive definite matrices.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Literature-1","page":"Overview","title":"Literature","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"<ul>\n  <li id=\"Betancourt2017\">[<a>Betancourt, 2017</a>]\n    M. Betancourt, “A Conceptual Introduction to Hamiltonian Monte Carlo,”\n    <i>arXiv [stat]</i>, 2017.\n    arXiv: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1701.02434\">1701.02434</a>.\n  </li>\n  <li id=\"Byrne2013\">[<a>Byrne and Girolami, 2013</a>]\n    S. Byrne and M. Girolami, “Geodesic Monte Carlo on Embedded Manifolds,”\n    <i>Scandinavian Journal of Statistics</i>, vol. 40, no. 4, pp. 825–845,\n    2013.\n    doi: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1111/sjos.12036\">10.1111/sjos.12036</a>.\n    arXiv: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1301.6064\">1301.6064</a>.\n  </li>\n</ul>","category":"page"}]
